<br>
Charm is a debate I don't want to get into... But I have to &quot;agree&quot; with you to an extent.  <br>
<br>
Our pets are really just an elemental that the mage has &quot;Charmed&quot;. However, when the game was first released our pets were considered too powerful and their damage output was nerfed (in half of what they would normally do).<br>
<br>
I don't want to see charm nerfed in its resists or breaks.  Charm is just too fookin useful in higher end encounters.  There is a big risk for that mob to tear through the enchanter when charm breaks.  And you never know when charm can break.<br>
<br>
Now as far as Dire Charm, this is way overpowered compared to other classes abilities.  Chanters can charm mobs that quad for 200+ for KT fights and such.  There is very little risk to this for the chanter.  I don't think this should be nerfed.  Instead, we should be given a class ability to compare to this.  An ability that uber buffs our pets.  Say adds 2-3k HP, doubles the max output damage, adds str, dex, agi to the pet.  I know its a dream.. but it was a good dream<br>
<br>
