<br>
if you can't:<br>
<br>
A) mez the mob<br>
B) stun the mob<br>
C) recharm the mob<br>
<br>
You have to run away, which is something a mage has to do every time he encounters more than 1 blue mob.<br>
<br>
If anything I almost think the situations should be reversed...<br>
<br>
Magician gets a 'charm' level pet, but in doing so, receives HUGE penalties(including the charm penalties) and his current penalties. <br>
<br>
While the enchanter would receive a pet about as strong as current mage pets. Due to the nature of the spells this seems unrealistic, but from a balancing standpoint it sure makes a hella more sense to me, considering all the other things an enchanter has to offer.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uenchanta.showPublicProfile?language=EN>enchanta</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(5/15/02 10:23:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=207.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: charm</span><hr size=1> watch out druids/wizards, quad kiting is next! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
